<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:23AM CDT until July 18 at 3:45AM CDT by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 345 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN MONROE AND EASTERN ARKANSAS COUNTIES...
At 323 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Clarendon to 7 miles east of Almyra to near De
Witt, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Gillett...                        St. Charles...
De Witt...                        Merrisach Lake...
Ethel...                          De Luce...
Casscoe...                        Crocketts Bluff...
Tichnor...                        Ragtown...
Indian Bay...                     Weber...
Lawrenceville...                  Cross Roads in Monroe County...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
